Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should... hurry up and run...!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.67,0:00:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police are coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.05,0:00:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.84,0:00:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dresden...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.59,0:00:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait at the train station...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and give me the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.31,0:00:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.02,0:00:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cedok Bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.61,0:00:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Three Frogs...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.19,0:00:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my father also said this...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.16,0:00:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If the monster you are after is a twin..."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.12,0:00:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"the mother of the twins..."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.00,0:00:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"is alive in Prague."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.72,0:02:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.68,0:02:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.81,0:02:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.77,0:02:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.32,0:02:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.02,0:02:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.65,0:02:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.72,0:02:29.47,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,75)\pos(353,356)}Grimmer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.91,0:02:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's it going, Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.99,0:02:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you able to find what you were looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.66,0:02:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the unification of the East and West...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.42,0:02:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the school system was completely changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.34,0:02:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that's the only old material we have left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.30,0:02:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you for your trouble, Director Albrecht.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.38,0:02:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually rare to see this much left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.01,0:02:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since after the Berlin Wall came down...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:02:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,most of the sensitive documents\Nof old East Germany disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.48,0:03:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.02,0:03:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's certain that juveniles were oppressed\Nin the orphanages of old East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.28,0:03:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.57,0:03:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's really hard to find documents to prove that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.41,0:03:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd imagine so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.16,0:03:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The orphanages of old East Germany were...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.37,0:03:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,often under the jurisdiction of the\NMinistry, of Health and Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.46,0:03:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem children were those whose parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.71,0:03:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were criminals, anti-government advocates, spies,\Nillegal immigrants, or unsuccessful refugees.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.05,0:03:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Among the orphanages that housed\Nthose types of children...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.05,0:03:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was a Kinderheim with a really bad reputation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.41,0:03:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,under the jurisdiction of the \N Ministry of Domestic Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.98,0:03:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that special orphanage...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.10,0:03:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm interested in the poor treatment and unlawful\Npersonality corrections that were conducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.19,0:03:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I want to uncover as many details as I can about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.57,0:03:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To find out exactly what went on in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.70,0:03:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.58,0:04:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's quite an investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.79,0:04:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone involved was either exiled or silenced, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.50,0:04:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.42,0:04:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The school nurse, Mr. Schnur, was involved as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.55,0:04:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Schnur?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.72,0:04:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was part of the teaching staff at Kinderheim\N62 in old East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked for an interview, but I was rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.69,0:04:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.40,0:04:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a chance Mr. Schnur was abusing children\Nwhen he was in old East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.99,0:04:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, may I make copies of these?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.95,0:04:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, sure! Go ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.71,0:04:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer, you're a journalist who\Nwas born in old West Germany, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.50,0:04:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was a reporter for a newspaper\Nin Leipzig on this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.09,0:04:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know people fighting for human\Nrights came from the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.93,0:04:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.52,0:05:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was traveling the world as an overseas\Ncorrespondent back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a job given to me by the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.82,0:05:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.53,0:05:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.74,0:05:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.16,0:05:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lot of luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of documents I found in various\Nplaces in old East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to a good report.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.80,0:05:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, where are you headed now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prague, in the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.09,0:05:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for all your help, Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.90,0:05:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They got you pretty bad back there, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, they took your shoes, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.16,0:06:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop crying already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.51,0:06:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People can live without shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we were all born with bare feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.39,0:06:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,those who pick on others by taking away their shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.07,0:06:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.07,0:06:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to cry because of such losers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.95,0:06:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.14,0:07:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it hard to walk in them because they're too big?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.08,0:07:06.22,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,114)\pos(353,366)}Dresden-Station
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.86,0:07:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.40,0:07:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.78,0:07:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.91,0:07:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.82,0:07:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.45,0:07:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in some trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.45,0:07:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bag that had my passport in it was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.29,0:07:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your passport?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.67,0:07:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that {\i1}is{\i0} a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.09,0:07:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was on my way to see my little sister in Vienna...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.42,0:07:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, I received a call saying\Nthat my sister had collapsed, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.72,0:07:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She collapsed?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.10,0:07:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you have to hurry up and get to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should go to the police right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, I've already done that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.44,0:07:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing is... my sister doesn't have the\Nmoney to cover her medical expenses...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.19,0:07:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. That's awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.82,0:08:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my wallet was also in the bag that was stolen...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go now, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I could just send her the money, she'll be saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.83,0:08:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, I can't even do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.37,0:08:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! I don't need that much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.09,0:08:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I need is enough to get her to a\Nhospital to have her looked at...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.18,0:08:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only give you this much...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.72,0:08:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.72,0:08:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Danke schon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.93,0:08:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pay you back, I swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.48,0:08:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please write your address on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.52,0:08:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.36,0:08:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it'll save your sister, then it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.36,0:08:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.53,0:08:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God bless you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of your little sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.16,0:08:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you give money to someone like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.50,0:08:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was an obvious lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.87,0:08:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.04,0:08:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys are always looking\Nfor marks at the train station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.34,0:09:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't let them trick you like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.09,0:09:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was tricked...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.01,0:09:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Express line to Prague will depart\Nfrom Platform Seven at 3:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.70,0:09:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.99,0:09:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That really helped. Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.12,0:09:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.05,0:09:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:09:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.52,0:09:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.90,0:10:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.57,0:10:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.51,0:10:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Japanese, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.63,0:10:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konnichiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.72,0:10:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.26,0:10:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.81,0:10:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.18,0:10:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how many years it's been?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was 1982...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.77,0:10:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yes. I went to Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.90,0:10:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember I got a lot of things like wiretaps\Nand high tech equipment and material.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.78,0:10:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I think a song like this was popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.95,0:10:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.45,0:10:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"At the road to the cemetery in the north was..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.25,0:11:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.50,0:11:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In the north..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.21,0:11:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the bar street.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.05,0:11:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.59,0:11:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"At the bar street in the north was..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.06,0:11:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there were robots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.27,0:11:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My boy was so happy when I bought him a plastic model.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.85,0:11:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's your child now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.56,0:11:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.03,0:11:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Border security check.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to inspect your passports.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.41,0:11:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.50,0:11:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Danke schon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.06,0:11:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Elbe River!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.77,0:12:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's the trout fishing this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.73,0:12:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.40,0:12:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught one about this big last year!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.90,0:12:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.95,0:12:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Danke schon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.59,0:12:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They know your passport is fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should run away from here, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.31,0:12:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.98,0:12:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.44,0:12:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the border police found out about your counterfeit\Npassport, and are on their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.94,0:12:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should run away, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.95,0:13:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.91,0:13:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to pass through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.16,0:13:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.46,0:13:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My bag is so big, it got stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.84,0:13:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not budging at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.50,0:13:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, what in the world are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.51,0:13:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, please don't be so rough!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.38,0:13:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's in that thing, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.59,0:13:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valuables.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.98,0:13:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm free!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.36,0:13:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what happened to\Nthe man who was just here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.99,0:13:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was an Oriental man in this room with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.32,0:13:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.41,0:13:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he went to the dining car?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, check that car over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.08,0:13:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is passenger car two!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.41,0:13:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.50,0:13:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Oriental passenger is using a counterfeit passport!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.38,0:13:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.96,0:14:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.26,0:14:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.03,0:14:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done! Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.58,0:14:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't coming this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.17,0:14:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got off the train because it stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.17,0:14:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I haven't introduced myself yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.34,0:14:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.13,0:14:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.64,0:14:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you like me to show you\Nto the border, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this place very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.07,0:15:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because I come here to fish quite often.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.11,0:15:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although climbing the mountain may be hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.07,0:15:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the scenery you'll get to see is well worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.16,0:15:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you helping me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.13,0:15:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I used to live in old East Germany,\NI worked for a newspaper company.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.67,0:15:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a freelance journalist now, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.97,0:15:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've read all the articles about you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.18,0:15:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because I find you interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.72,0:15:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In old East Germany, false charges\Nwere an everyday occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.31,0:15:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This political prisoner was falsely accused...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.02,0:15:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That murderer was also innocent...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.69,0:15:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this and that, I can distinguish between a\Nreal criminal and someone wrongfully accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.74,0:15:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.75,0:15:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you stop calling me doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're an excellent neurosurgeon,\Naren't you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.38,0:16:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no longer a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.48,0:16:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.89,0:16:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a great view isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.90,0:16:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From here, we'll be able to see them coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.94,0:16:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.70,0:16:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a break here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.45,0:16:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like a sandwich?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have wine as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.29,0:16:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I've got this delicious cheese...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.42,0:16:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... uh... I don't have that much time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.80,0:16:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun's still high in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.63,0:16:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better to cross the border when it's dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.56,0:16:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Picnics are so much fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.31,0:17:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to do something like this once\Nin a while, don't you think, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.60,0:17:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such beautiful scenery!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.52,0:17:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And such delicious food!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.53,0:17:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Times like these are when you feel happy to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.45,0:17:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I look up to doctors like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.91,0:17:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even for a journalist like myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.00,0:17:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might be able to give people the joy of\Nbeing alive if I can write a good article.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.13,0:17:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can give people life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.51,0:17:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.97,0:17:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shot someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.02,0:17:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last month, in Munich...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.36,0:17:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shot someone for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.16,0:17:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I shot, my hands kept shaking...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't aim very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.29,0:18:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But once I pulled the trigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.58,0:18:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my hands stopped shaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.22,0:18:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.01,0:18:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's still another man out there I have to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.60,0:18:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no longer... a doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.49,0:18:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I come to the Elbe River, I think to myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.12,0:18:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I wanted my kid to fish here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.13,0:18:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The child who passed away...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.92,0:18:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can catch trout this big!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.59,0:19:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He passed away without knowing how fun fishing is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.22,0:19:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there had been a doctor like you nearby, then perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.85,0:19:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his life would've been saved, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.99,0:19:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.03,0:19:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really can catch trout this big!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.42,0:19:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you cross that mountain, you'll\Nbe at the Czech Republic border.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.04,0:19:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you cross the border, you'll\Ncome to a path in the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.17,0:19:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you can probably hitch a ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.80,0:19:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to head back to the station now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.89,0:19:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.97,0:19:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've really helped me, Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.51,0:19:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you luck, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.86,0:19:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we meet again, let's have another picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.16,0:20:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.58,0:20:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is burdened with different sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.29,0:20:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those sins will never disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.08,0:20:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you still have to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:42.05,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,75)\pos(356,374)}Prague (Czech Republic)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.03,0:20:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.87,0:20:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, it's simply beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.75,0:20:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my first time here, but Prague at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.04,0:20:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,looks just like a town out of a fairy tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.60,0:21:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, may I sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.56,0:21:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.94,0:21:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've really become fond of this town!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.48,0:21:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Mr. Petrov, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.53,0:21:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've bought yourself a Russian nationality...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.66,0:21:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are now living in the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to ask you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.70,0:21:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please help me out, Mr. Petrov?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.04,0:21:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your real name is Mr. Reinhard Biermann...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.09,0:21:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a special orphanage\Nin East Germany, wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.84,0:21:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A testing site to scientifically correct\Nthe children's personalities...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.39,0:21:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.02,0:21:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the director there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.36,0:21:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.32,0:22:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since you were the director, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.28,0:22:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.95,0:22:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that place in old East Berlin?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.87,0:22:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At Kinderheim 511?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.89,0:22:31.06,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:44.49,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:44.49,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.49,0:22:47.45,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:23:01.13,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:23:01.13,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.73,0:23:25.99,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.99,0:23:34.41,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.41,0:23:36.87,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.39,0:23:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
